m, examining their interrelationship and revealing how she brought two worlds—the poetic and the political—together. Counting Dreams illustrates Bōtō's significant role in the loyalist movement, depicting the adventurous life of a complex woman in Japan on the cusp of the Meiji Restoration.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aBuddhist nunszJapanvBiography. 0aWakaxHistory and criticism. 4aAsian Studies. 4aHistory. 4aLiterary Studies. 7aHISTORY / Asia / Japan.2bisacsh  aNomura Bōtō, loyalist movement in western Japan, waka poetry of the bakumatsu, women’s diaries of the bakumatsu, Buddhist nuns in the loyalist movement.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073908408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021 Englishz978311075408708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021z9783110753851oZDB-23-DEG0 cprintz978150175999440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501760013?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501760013423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501760013/original  a978-3-11-073908-4  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075408-7  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DEGb2021